1
01:57:32,098 --> 01:57:34,098
Not my horse!
I need it!

2
01:57:34,726 --> 01:57:35,560
[DWARVES MURMUR]

3
01:57:36,061 --> 01:57:37,270
You're not leaving us?

4
01:57:37,521 --> 01:57:39,272
I would not do this unless I had to.

5
01:57:45,904 --> 01:57:47,197
You've changed...

6
01:57:47,447 --> 01:57:49,199
...Bilbo Baggins.

7
01:57:50,575 --> 01:57:53,620
You're not the same Hobbit
as the one who left the Shire.

8
01:57:56,540 --> 01:57:58,083
I was going to tell you.

9
01:58:01,711 --> 01:58:02,837
I...

10
01:58:05,715 --> 01:58:07,801
...found something in the Goblin tunnels.

11
01:58:08,051 --> 01:58:09,386
Found what?

12
01:58:14,140 --> 01:58:15,976
What did you find?

13
01:58:19,479 --> 01:58:20,689
My courage.

14
01:58:23,483 --> 01:58:25,527
Good. Well, that's good.

15
01:58:28,363 --> 01:58:30,198
You'll need it.

16
01:58:30,490 --> 01:58:34,452
I'll be waiting for you at the overlook,
before the slopes of Erebor.

17
01:58:34,703 --> 01:58:37,080
Keep the map and key safe.

18
01:58:37,330 --> 01:58:40,292
Do not enter that mountain without me.

19
01:58:46,214 --> 01:58:49,467
This is not the Greenwood of old.

20
01:58:49,718 --> 01:58:53,013
The very air of the forest
is heavy with illusion.

21
01:58:53,263 --> 01:58:55,974
It'll seek to enter your mind
and lead you astray.

22
01:58:56,433 --> 01:58:58,143
"Lead us astray"?

23
01:58:58,602 --> 01:58:59,936
What does that mean?

24
01:59:00,312 --> 01:59:03,440
GANDALF:
You must stay on the path. Do not leave it.

25
01:59:03,898 --> 01:59:07,444
If you do, you'll never find it again.

26
01:59:09,112 --> 01:59:11,573
No matter what may come,
stay on the path!

27
01:59:11,823 --> 01:59:14,993
Come on. We must reach the mountain
before the sun sets on Durin's Day.

28
01:59:15,243 --> 01:59:16,244
BILBO: Durin's Day?
BOFUR: Let's go.

29
01:59:16,494 --> 01:59:18,997
THORIN: It is our one chance
to find the hidden door.

30
01:59:29,758 --> 01:59:31,384
THORIN:
The path turns this way.

31
01:59:57,410 --> 01:59:58,620
This way.

32
02:00:07,212 --> 02:00:10,382
BOFUR:
Air. I need air.

33
02:00:10,632 --> 02:00:12,036
OIN:
My head...

34
02:00:12,237 --> 02:00:14,010
...it's swimming!
What's happening?

35
02:00:14,260 --> 02:00:15,678
Keep moving.

36
02:00:16,096 --> 02:00:17,138
Nori...

37
02:00:18,382 --> 02:00:19,516
...why have we stopped?

38
02:00:19,766 --> 02:00:22,602
The path...
It's disappeared.

39
02:00:22,852 --> 02:00:23,992
DWALIN:
What's going on?

40
02:00:24,604 --> 02:00:26,689
OIN:
We've lost the path!

41
02:00:26,940 --> 02:00:28,199
THORIN:
Find it.

42
02:00:28,400 --> 02:00:31,319
All of you, look. Look for the path!

43
02:00:36,908 --> 02:00:38,326
[GROANS]

44
02:00:40,453 --> 02:00:42,747
I don't remember this bit.

45
02:00:42,997 --> 02:00:44,624
None of it's familiar.

46
02:00:44,874 --> 02:00:46,626
DORI:
It's got to be here.

47
02:00:47,335 --> 02:00:48,753
THORIN:
What hour is it?

48
02:00:49,003 --> 02:00:52,507
I do not know. I do not even know
what day it is.

49
02:00:53,133 --> 02:00:55,677
THORIN:
Is there no end to this accursed forest?!

50
02:01:10,109 --> 02:01:11,484
VOICE [WHISPERING]:
Attercop.

51
02:01:39,387 --> 02:01:42,223
- Look.
- A tobacco pouch.

52
02:01:42,474 --> 02:01:44,893
There's Dwarves in these woods.

53
02:01:45,143 --> 02:01:47,770
Dwarves from the Blue Mountains,
no less.

54
02:01:48,021 --> 02:01:49,689
This is exactly the same as mine.

55
02:01:49,939 --> 02:01:52,609
Because it is yours. Do you understand?

56
02:01:52,859 --> 02:01:54,652
We're going around in circles.
We are lost.

57
02:01:54,903 --> 02:01:56,946
THORIN:
We are not lost. We keep heading east.

58
02:01:57,197 --> 02:01:59,824
OIN:
But which way is east? We've lost the sun.

59
02:02:00,074 --> 02:02:01,451
DWALIN:
I thought you were the expert.

60
02:02:02,577 --> 02:02:03,803
The sun.

61
02:02:04,370 --> 02:02:07,582
We have to find the sun.

62
02:02:09,417 --> 02:02:10,634
Up there.

63
02:02:10,835 --> 02:02:13,421
We need to get above the canopy.

64
02:02:13,671 --> 02:02:15,757
[DWARVES CLAMORING]

65
02:02:16,007 --> 02:02:17,133
[VOICES WHISPERING INDISTINCTLY]

66
02:02:17,425 --> 02:02:19,344
What was that?

67
02:02:20,553 --> 02:02:23,431
Enough! Quiet! All of you!

68
02:02:25,391 --> 02:02:27,143
[WHISPERING]
We're being watched.

69
02:02:50,124 --> 02:02:51,459
[SIGHS]

70
02:03:01,052 --> 02:03:02,387
[CHUCKLES]

71
02:03:15,567 --> 02:03:17,318
I can see a lake!

72
02:03:18,152 --> 02:03:20,321
And a river.

73
02:03:22,031 --> 02:03:23,658
And the Lonely Mountain.

74
02:03:24,117 --> 02:03:25,910
We're almost there!

75
02:03:27,829 --> 02:03:29,163
Can you hear me?

76
02:03:30,415 --> 02:03:32,584
I know which way to go!

77
02:03:32,834 --> 02:03:34,460
[BRANCHES SNAPPING]

78
02:03:35,920 --> 02:03:37,046
Hello?

79
02:03:41,551 --> 02:03:43,553
[BRANCHES CONTINUE SNAPPING]

80
02:03:46,389 --> 02:03:47,599
Hello.

81
02:03:59,652 --> 02:04:00,612
Oh, no.

82
02:04:00,862 --> 02:04:03,072
Oh, come on.
[YELLS]

83
02:04:07,994 --> 02:04:09,362
[CHITTERS]

84
02:04:11,122 --> 02:04:11,964
[ROARS]

85
02:04:12,165 --> 02:04:13,166
[SCREAMS]

86
02:05:40,920 --> 02:05:43,548
SPIDER 1:
Kill them! Kill them.

87
02:05:43,798 --> 02:05:45,842
Eat them now,
while their blood is running.

88
02:05:46,092 --> 02:05:49,595
SPIDER 2: Their hide is tough,
but there's good juice inside.

89
02:05:49,846 --> 02:05:52,765
SPIDER 1: Stick it again.
Stick it again. Finish it off.

90
02:05:53,891 --> 02:05:55,643
SPIDER 2:
The meat's alive and kicking!

91
02:05:55,893 --> 02:05:57,478
SPIDER 1:
Kill him. Kill them now.

92
02:05:57,729 --> 02:05:59,313
Let us feast.

93
02:05:59,564 --> 02:06:00,773
Feast! Feast!

94
02:06:01,023 --> 02:06:03,109
SPIDER 3:
Feast! Feast!

95
02:06:04,485 --> 02:06:05,903
SPIDER 4:
Eat them alive!

96
02:06:06,154 --> 02:06:08,197
Feast!

97
02:06:13,035 --> 02:06:14,328
[STICK CLATTERS]

98
02:06:14,579 --> 02:06:16,414
SPIDER 2: What is it?
SPIDER 1: What is it?

99
02:06:18,291 --> 02:06:20,501
SPIDER 4:
Eat them alive!

100
02:06:23,755 --> 02:06:25,882
SPIDER 3:
Fat and juicy.

101
02:06:28,968 --> 02:06:31,679
Just a little taste.

102
02:06:33,014 --> 02:06:33,681
[HISSING]

103
02:06:42,356 --> 02:06:44,692
Curse it! Where is it?! Where is it?!

104
02:06:45,919 --> 02:06:47,195
Here.

105
02:06:48,154 --> 02:06:51,199
Ah! It stings!
It stings!

106
02:06:57,163 --> 02:06:58,456
Sting.

107
02:06:59,415 --> 02:07:00,708
That's a good name.

108
02:07:02,502 --> 02:07:03,628
Sting.

109
02:07:21,875 --> 02:07:23,543
GLOIN:
You all right there, Bofur?

110
02:07:23,744 --> 02:07:25,365
BALIN: I'm all right!
THORIN: Get it off me!

111
02:07:25,566 --> 02:07:26,845
BOFUR:
Where's Bilbo?

112
02:07:27,279 --> 02:07:28,285
BILBO:
I'm up here!

113
02:07:28,486 --> 02:07:29,486
[BILBO YELLS]

114
02:07:32,824 --> 02:07:33,991
[BILBO SCREAMS]

115
02:07:46,003 --> 02:07:47,505
[DWARVES CLAMOR]

